# CLIP ChangeLog for x11-misc/xscreensaver

*xscreensaver-5.36 (26 Oct 2017)

  26 Oct 2017; Nicolas Godinho <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xscreensaver-5.36.ebuild, -xscreensaver-5.15-r10.ebuild:
  Bump to latest stable with some adaptations to avoid compiling all the hacks
  (i.e. the fancy screensaver animations) which are useless in the context of
  CLIP.

*xscreensaver-5.15-r10 (27 Jun 2014)

  27 Jun 2014; Tony Cheneau <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xscreensaver-5.15-r10.ebuild, -xscreensaver-5.15-r9.ebuild:
  Fix for xscreensaver-settime.sh - user input was not parsed correctly
  and caused the screen to lock out in a matter of seconds.

*xscreensaver-5.15-r9 (18 Mar 2014)

  18 Mar 2014; Hugo Chargois <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xscreensaver-5.15-r9.ebuild, -xscreensaver-5.15-r8.ebuild,
  +files/xscreensaver-5.15-clip-no-detect-overlap.patch:
  Fix xscreensaver not blanking all the monitors when they overlap.
  This is apparently a "feature", so the fix is simply to not
  detect overlapping monitors.

  02 Sep 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  xscreensaver-5.15-r8.ebuild:
  Do not depend on appres, etc. on clip-devstation either.

*xscreensaver-5.15-r8 (13 Mar 2013)

  13 Mar 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xscreensaver-5.15-r8.ebuild, -xscreensaver-5.15-r7.ebuild:
  files/xscreensaver-settime.sh:
  Fix initial timeout value, which was set to 0 following previous
  revision.

*xscreensaver-5.15-r7 (25 Feb 2013)

  25 Feb 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xscreensaver-5.15-r7.ebuild, -xscreensaver-5.15-r6.ebuild,
  -files/xscreensaver, files/xscreensaver-settime.sh:
  Revert to a simple, per-user setting for lock delay - the 
  admin/user separation generally leaves users puzzled.

*xscreensaver-5.15-r6 (23 Jan 2013)

  23 Jan 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +xscreensaver-5.15-r6.ebuild, -xscreensaver-5.15-r5.ebuild,
  files/XScreenSaver:
  Disable captureStderr to avoid troubling end-users with cryptic
  messages.

*xscreensaver-5.15-r5 (14 Nov 2012)

